textBeforeTable: Overall Male Winners wallacewilliams@msn.com or e-mail: http://virginislandspace.org For information, contact The Virgin Islands Pace Runners at 643-2557 or logon to http://virginislandspace.org For complete results logon to Ana Guiterrez Wittam, the first and only female to compete in the Olympic Games marathon for the Virgin Islands (1992 Barcelona Olympics), had a bold performance in a very competitive race with visiting Jodi Ahlstrom over the beautiful but very tuff St. Croix Ironman run course. The two battled all the way and only two seconds separated them at the end with Guiterrez winning with a time of 22:47, Ahlstrom was second in 22:49. Defending champion Mireille Smith was third in 23:22.             Virgin Islands long distance record holder, Billy Bohlke took first place with a time of 18:23 in the 24th Paradise 5K on Thursday, a tune-up event for The Ironman 70.3 St. Croix Triathlon. It was the second win in three races at the 5k distance that Bohlke has met 14 year-old Malique Smith of the St. Croix Track Club at the distance. Smith surprised all when he beat Bohlke at the tape in the UVI/Queen Mary Highway 5K in March. It was all about experience during the race at sunset over the Buccaneer Resort and the route for the big triathlon, as Bohlke led at the mile mark by only a couple of seconds with a 5:16 mile and held the lead by surging on the hills. Smith, who competed
